Language Familiarity:
 - I reviewed the fundamentals of C and C++, which included basic syntax, 
   if statements, loops, input/output handling, and functions, to ensure that I can
   easily write code before I begin working on this project.
Online Communication:
  - I focused on how users connect to servers in order to properly
    process chat applications, and looked into how clients can communicate with
    other clients. I ended up choosing a client-server model for the purposes
    of this project, since it is more of an introductory level project.
TCP Sockets:
  - I learned that TCP, which is the Transmission Control Protocol, 
    ensures that two machines, which use an IP address and a port number can
    effectively communicate, since sockets are the endpoints when two machines
    attempt to communicate.
  - I learned some basic socket operations such as socket() to create a socket, and
    listen() to look out for incoming connections, accept() to accept a connection, 
    and close() to close a connection. I will continue learning the commands so I can
    complete the project with ease.
